1
00:00:00,043 --> 00:00:40,043
Officail Website : kissasian.be  Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

2
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:46,343
[This drama is fictional, and any resemblance
to real people or events is coincidental.]

3
00:00:46,367 --> 00:00:48,709
[Episode 7]

4
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:51,143
If Kim Yeong Ran doesn't
show up immediately,

5
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:54,833
I can't guarantee her mother's life.

6
00:00:55,467 --> 00:00:57,576
I'm the late Chairman Ga Sung Ho's lawyer.

7
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,309
I'm not her mother's lawyer.

8
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:01,100
Do whatever you want.

9
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:07,700
[Ms. Bu Se Mi]

10
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:28,933
[Gaseong Art Center]

11
00:02:18,633 --> 00:02:20,600
Save me.

12
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,733
Save me.

13
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:29,233
Your daughter takes
after you, cold-hearted.

14
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:33,233
Says she doesn't care
whether her mother lives or dies.

15
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,076
I'll do anything.

16
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:40,409
Just please save me.

17
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:41,709
Madam.

18
00:02:41,733 --> 00:02:43,676
Anything?

19
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,633
Yes, I mean it.

20
00:02:49,867 --> 00:02:51,500
Then

21
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:55,300
can you kill your own daughter too?

22
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:18,809
Where is this place?

23
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:20,533
What's this?

24
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,833
What's going on?

25
00:03:24,733 --> 00:03:26,376
What is this?

26
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,576
Where am I?

27
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,643
Hey! What's this?

28
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:30,709
What's this?

29
00:03:30,733 --> 00:03:32,609
What is this?

30
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:34,309
What's going on?

31
00:03:34,333 --> 00:03:36,033
Hey!

32
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:41,309
Honey, untie this for me.

33
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:42,676
Honey!

34
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:45,876
Seon Yeong, Seon Woo!

35
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:49,576
Mom, why is Dad here?

36
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:52,176
You two, watch carefully.

37
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:54,643
This is what happens
when you don't listen to Mom.

38
00:03:54,667 --> 00:03:56,433
Seon Yeong.

39
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:03,767
Save me.

40
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:07,743
What is this?

41
00:04:07,767 --> 00:04:08,843
What is this?

42
00:04:08,867 --> 00:04:10,676
What's going on!

43
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,143
What's this?

44
00:04:12,167 --> 00:04:13,800
Hey!

45
00:04:34,467 --> 00:04:36,100
Jeon Dong Min?

46
00:06:41,433 --> 00:06:43,909
Hey, catch.

47
00:06:43,933 --> 00:06:45,809
You want me to drive?

48
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:49,976
Yeah, I've been feeling stiff lately,

49
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:53,909
so I thought I'd jog
to the greenhouse for exercise.

50
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:55,533
Take the car and come.

51
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:03,067
Oh, you're copying Ms. Bu Se Mi now?

52
00:07:21,767 --> 00:07:24,243
Are you following me?

53
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:25,676
No.

54
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:28,500
I'm just on my way to the greenhouse.

55
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:37,976
Is your hand okay?

56
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,709
Oh, this?

57
00:07:39,733 --> 00:07:41,433
It's nothing serious.

58
00:07:42,733 --> 00:07:45,909
It feels great to run like this
in the morning after so long, right?

59
00:07:45,933 --> 00:07:47,600
The air is refreshing too.

60
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:51,309
Running together is
better than alone, right?

61
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,109
Yes.

62
00:07:53,133 --> 00:07:54,143
By the way, Mr. Jeon.

63
00:07:54,167 --> 00:07:55,343
Yes?

64
00:07:55,367 --> 00:07:57,700
We already passed your greenhouse.

65
00:08:00,467 --> 00:08:02,176
Ah.

66
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:05,767
Oh, I usually drive, that's why.

67
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,767
I'll go ahead first.

68
00:08:09,567 --> 00:08:11,733
See you at home later.

69
00:08:21,967 --> 00:08:24,300
I'm really not like what
I used to be anymore.

70
00:08:33,167 --> 00:08:35,676
Ms. Bu, you're working out again today.

71
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:37,243
Oh, have you seen Dong Min?

72
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:39,876
Oh, Mr. Jeon went that way earlier.

73
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:42,209
Why that way?

74
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:48,176
He suddenly decided to start working out
this morning, made such a fuss about it.

75
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:50,900
By the way, Miss, well...

76
00:08:52,433 --> 00:08:57,267
What kind of guys does Hye Ji like?

77
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:01,109
Ask her directly.

78
00:09:01,133 --> 00:09:04,233
But I'm too shy to ask her myself.

79
00:09:13,667 --> 00:09:16,076
Tae Min, Tae Min.

80
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:20,067
Bu Se Mi.

81
00:09:23,133 --> 00:09:25,276
You.

82
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:28,143
Someone's coming.

83
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:30,609
Be careful.

84
00:09:30,633 --> 00:09:32,267
Pardon?

85
00:09:33,933 --> 00:09:35,567
Let's go.

86
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:52,976
You have a visitor.

87
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,600
Visitor?

88
00:09:58,633 --> 00:10:00,267
Who?

89
00:10:07,367 --> 00:10:09,943
It's been a while, Vice President.

90
00:10:09,967 --> 00:10:11,743
Lee Don.

91
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:14,376
How did you find this place?

92
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,443
It was you, right?

93
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:17,743
You're the one who put me in here?

94
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:19,809
Let's talk nicely, please.

95
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:22,976
I'm a believer in non-violence.

96
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,809
Let go of me!

97
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:26,809
It took some work to find this place.

98
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:30,067
She hid you away quite thoroughly.

99
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:34,043
What nonsense is this?

100
00:10:34,067 --> 00:10:35,867
Doesn't this place

101
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,533
feel familiar to you?

102
00:10:45,567 --> 00:10:47,300
No way.

103
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,643
Did my sister really do this?

104
00:10:51,667 --> 00:10:54,876
You were going to sell the company, which
is like her life, to Chinese investors.

105
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,809
Do you really think
Professor Ga would let that pass

106
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:59,000
just because you are her brother?

107
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,009
So, what do you want to say?

108
00:11:02,033 --> 00:11:04,509
I'll get you out of this
hospital immediately,

109
00:11:04,533 --> 00:11:07,209
restore your damaged reputation,

110
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:10,543
and make you CEO of Gaseong Group.

111
00:11:10,567 --> 00:11:12,576
Vice President.

112
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:15,109
Shall we join forces?

113
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:16,867
Forces?

114
00:11:18,033 --> 00:11:19,700
Are you insane?

115
00:11:36,567 --> 00:11:39,576
[Hospital Admission Form]

116
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:43,167
[Guardian: Ga Seon Yeong]

117
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:45,733
This...

118
00:11:48,033 --> 00:11:51,943
Is my sister really doing this to me?

119
00:11:51,967 --> 00:11:53,576
This.

120
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:56,443
Is my own sister really doing this? Huh?

121
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:57,643
You have no parents,

122
00:11:57,667 --> 00:11:58,909
no spouse,

123
00:11:58,933 --> 00:12:02,500
and Professor Ga is your only guardian.

124
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:08,000
You know you can't discharge yourself
without a guardian, right?

125
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,876
How could my sister do this to me?

126
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:13,176
How could she!

127
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,576
I know everything.

128
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:17,567
I know what she did.

129
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:19,943
Hey, Attorney Lee.

130
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:21,709
Do you know any reporters?

131
00:12:21,733 --> 00:12:25,809
I'm going to blow everything wide open.

132
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,676
Vice President.

133
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:29,609
Mind if I hear that story too?

134
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:35,133
Actually, I might be able to
get you out of here for sure.

135
00:12:44,533 --> 00:12:46,333
Hey.

136
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:49,700
Do you think I'm stupid?

137
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:54,200
Why would I believe a word you say?

138
00:12:57,533 --> 00:12:59,533
Then there's nothing more to say.

139
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:03,309
As Chairman Ga Sung Ho's lawyer,

140
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:05,900
I've shown enough goodwill.

141
00:13:10,067 --> 00:13:11,667
I'll take my leave now.

142
00:13:22,633 --> 00:13:24,543
Go back inside.

143
00:13:24,567 --> 00:13:28,309
What should we play
in the Strawberry Class?

144
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:30,009
Let's run a hundred laps together.

145
00:13:30,033 --> 00:13:31,624
Okay.

146
00:13:31,648 --> 00:13:34,343
Look what they're doing.

147
00:13:34,367 --> 00:13:37,209
- Hello.
- Hello.

148
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,976
Miss, come here for a second.

149
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:42,276
Strawberry Class kids, stay inside.

150
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:44,067
- Okay.
- Okay.

151
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:52,276
Miss, can I ask you a favor?

152
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:54,676
No, you may not.

153
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,743
No, absolutely not.

154
00:13:56,767 --> 00:13:58,609
Principal, what's wrong?

155
00:13:58,633 --> 00:14:01,043
Today's parent observation day, right?

156
00:14:01,067 --> 00:14:02,044
Yes.

157
00:14:02,068 --> 00:14:05,676
All the parents are dying
to see a class taught

158
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:08,000
by an Iseon Women's University graduate.

159
00:14:09,133 --> 00:14:10,609
What should we do, Miss?

160
00:14:10,633 --> 00:14:14,943
Would you like to give a class today?

161
00:14:14,967 --> 00:14:16,209
Oh, please.

162
00:14:16,233 --> 00:14:19,176
You said you'd handle
all observation classes alone.

163
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,543
Told us to stay quiet and not teach.

164
00:14:21,567 --> 00:14:22,709
Exactly.

165
00:14:22,733 --> 00:14:25,267
Yes, yes, I did say that.

166
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,009
However.

167
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:28,643
[The Sun and Moon Siblings]

168
00:14:28,667 --> 00:14:32,176
Today I, as principal,

169
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:35,343
will specially permit Ms. Bu Se Mi's class.

170
00:14:35,367 --> 00:14:38,243
Now, take this.

171
00:14:38,267 --> 00:14:41,176
Nod, just nod.

172
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:43,133
You can do it.

173
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:45,843
Principal.

174
00:14:45,867 --> 00:14:48,343
Shall I go ahead with
the ballet class then?

175
00:14:48,367 --> 00:14:50,100
I can do it!

176
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:56,343
Everyone, today we'll learn about 'plié'.

177
00:14:56,367 --> 00:14:58,609
Now, let's try following along.

178
00:14:58,633 --> 00:15:00,343
First, spread your legs like... no,

179
00:15:00,367 --> 00:15:02,909
spread your feet,

180
00:15:02,933 --> 00:15:05,776
hands together in front.

181
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:09,176
Plié.

182
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,776
Good job.

183
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,709
Now stand back up

184
00:15:13,733 --> 00:15:16,343
and plié.

185
00:15:16,367 --> 00:15:18,109
Excellent.

186
00:15:18,133 --> 00:15:20,876
Ah, moms,

187
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:23,209
please massage this part.

188
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:25,643
It's also great for blood circulation.

189
00:15:25,667 --> 00:15:30,167
Now, I'll take a photo of
each of you one by one.

190
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:35,843
Let's see who's doing well.

191
00:15:35,867 --> 00:15:37,509
Who wants to go first?

192
00:15:37,533 --> 00:15:39,443
Okay, plié.

193
00:15:39,467 --> 00:15:41,567
Oh, very good.

194
00:15:42,433 --> 00:15:44,743
So fast, thank you.

195
00:15:44,767 --> 00:15:47,609
Next one, plié.

196
00:15:47,633 --> 00:15:49,043
Ooh, excellent.

197
00:15:49,067 --> 00:15:50,443
Now, we're going to try

198
00:15:50,467 --> 00:15:54,943
a de... Demi-plié.

199
00:15:54,967 --> 00:15:56,709
Ready?

200
00:15:56,733 --> 00:15:59,776
After the plié here,

201
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:02,009
raise your arms sideways.

202
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:04,843
Now, stretch out your arm.

203
00:16:04,867 --> 00:16:08,509
Let's see whose armpits look nicest!

204
00:16:08,533 --> 00:16:10,176
Oh, lovely.

205
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,743
Wow, so beautiful.

206
00:16:11,767 --> 00:16:12,744
Oh, well done.

207
00:16:12,768 --> 00:16:16,509
'Long, long ago, when
tigers used to smoke.'

208
00:16:16,533 --> 00:16:18,843
'In a small hut deep in the mountains.'

209
00:16:18,867 --> 00:16:22,809
'A widowed mother lived there,
raising her two young children alone.'

210
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:27,643
'Every time she went to work,
she warned her children.'

211
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:32,843
'Kids, when Mommy's not home,
never open the door for anyone.'

212
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:36,143
'One day, their mother
did chores at a village feast.'

213
00:16:36,167 --> 00:16:38,443
'She received rice cakes as payment.'

214
00:16:38,467 --> 00:16:42,400
'Thinking of her children,
she hurried home.'

215
00:16:43,233 --> 00:16:46,900
'I need to give these
cakes to my babies quickly.'

216
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:55,143
'But on the shadowy mountain path,
there was a tiger as big as a house!'

217
00:16:55,167 --> 00:17:00,233
'The tiger growled,
raising its massive paws.'

218
00:17:03,367 --> 00:17:07,576
'Give me a rice cake, and I won't eat you.'

219
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:09,500
'Grrr!'

220
00:17:10,167 --> 00:17:11,967
'Grrr!'

221
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:16,576
'Trembling, the mother
handed over the rice cake.'

222
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:20,909
'The tiger ate the cake and slunk away.'

223
00:17:20,933 --> 00:17:22,176
'Phew.'

224
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:26,643
'As the mother calmed her racing heart
and crossed the next hill, '

225
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:31,943
'the tiger reappeared,
baring its sharp teeth.'

226
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:34,209
'Grrr!'

227
00:17:34,233 --> 00:17:39,033
'Give me a rice cake, and I won't eat you.'

228
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,843
'The sister became the sun,
and the brother became the moon.'

229
00:17:44,867 --> 00:17:48,800
'They lived happily ever after.'

230
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:53,676
Strawberry Class, everyone.

231
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:55,343
- Yes.
- Yes.

232
00:17:55,367 --> 00:17:58,909
If you're home alone
and a stranger asks to open the door,

233
00:17:58,933 --> 00:18:00,276
what should you do?

234
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:02,209
- No.
- Never let anyone in.

235
00:18:02,233 --> 00:18:05,943
- I must never open the door.
- No.

236
00:18:05,967 --> 00:18:07,909
Never ever.

237
00:18:07,933 --> 00:18:09,409
Alright.

238
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:14,467
This is Iseon Kindergarten's
unique interactive class!

239
00:18:15,233 --> 00:18:16,876
Strawberry Class.

240
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:18,609
One, two, three!

241
00:18:18,633 --> 00:18:21,133
- Grrr!
- Grrr!

242
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:25,367
What's going on?

243
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:29,200
That was great, Miss.

244
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,109
Sorry to interrupt.

245
00:18:32,133 --> 00:18:33,767
Ms. Bu Se Mi.

246
00:18:34,533 --> 00:18:36,167
Yes?

247
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:54,033
Daughter! My daughter!

248
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:21,809
Parents,

249
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:23,976
our next class is physical education.

250
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,776
Please follow us to the Apple Classroom
with your children.

251
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,176
Strawberry Class, move out!

252
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,376
- Move out.
- Move out.

253
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:33,443
Let's all do the pliés
we learned earlier as we go out.

254
00:19:33,467 --> 00:19:36,909
- Plié.
- Plié.

255
00:19:36,933 --> 00:19:39,033
Plié.

256
00:20:02,567 --> 00:20:04,567
Didn't you miss me?

257
00:20:15,233 --> 00:20:17,443
Yeong Ran.

258
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:21,200
Do you know how hard it was
for Mommy to come here?

259
00:20:22,567 --> 00:20:24,167
Whoa!

260
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:28,243
Yeong Ran.

261
00:20:28,267 --> 00:20:31,709
Shouldn't you worry about me
coming all this way like this?

262
00:20:31,733 --> 00:20:34,843
Is that how I raised you, Yeong Ran?

263
00:20:34,867 --> 00:20:37,376
Why are you rolling your eyes?

264
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:39,300
Well, you are Madam now...

265
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,876
Did Ga Seon Yeong send you?

266
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:45,843
How did you even get here? Huh?

267
00:20:45,867 --> 00:20:47,209
See this? This?

268
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:49,809
That witch Ga Seon Yeong did this to me.

269
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:52,176
I thought I was going to die.

270
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:55,943
I ran out without even having time
to dress properly.

271
00:20:55,967 --> 00:20:58,800
Ugh, this might leave a scar.

272
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:02,676
How did you find out I was here? Huh?

273
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:04,643
Yeong Ran.

274
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:07,643
Only the back of your
head was in the article,

275
00:21:07,667 --> 00:21:09,509
but I recognized you.

276
00:21:09,533 --> 00:21:11,176
Hey.

277
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:13,943
Turns out I have maternal instincts too.

278
00:21:13,967 --> 00:21:16,067
So I decided,

279
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:20,133
I deserve payback for raising you.

280
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:25,676
As payment, ever since I became an adult

281
